# TriFrame: Assembly-Free Metagenomic Functional Annotation

TriFrame is a deep learning model that takes raw metagenomic DNA reads (150вҖ“300 bp) and directly predicts functional annotations вҖ” EC numbers, KEGG orthologs, and COG categories вҖ” without requiring assembly, ORF prediction, or database alignment. The key challenge is that a random metagenomic read could originate from any of six reading frames (3 forward + 3 reverse complement) and may not even be protein-coding. TriFrame addresses this with two novel architectural components: **Frame Attention with Gating**, which learns to identify the correct coding frame(s), and **Cross-Resolution Attention**, which fuses nucleotide-level compositional signals with codon-level protein function signals at different granularities.

